OL,6,FMr Corrigan explained: "Tonnage
OL,7,Fcharges are applied at the Port of St
OL,8,FHelier - that's always been the case,
OL,9,Fand that's always passed through from
OL,10,Fthe ferry operator.
OL,12,F"The second aspect, which is the part
OL,13,Fwhich people consider to be more
OL,14,Fcontentious, is the unit charges per
OL,15,Ftrailer.
OL,17,F"They are charged both at Portsmouth
OL,18,FInternational Port and the Port of St
OL,19,FHelier, and they equate to about #68
OL,20,For so on each crossing.
